'''Warren Marie Jean-Pierre Zaïre-Emery''' (born 8 March 2006) is a French professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[midfielder]] for [[Ligue 1]] club [[Paris Saint-Germain FC|Paris Saint-Germain]] and the [[France national football team|France national team]].

A product of the [[Paris Saint-Germain FC Youth Academy|Paris Saint-Germain Youth Academy]], Zaïre-Emery made his professional debut for PSG in August 2022, becoming the club's youngest-ever player. In his debut season, he became the club's youngest-ever goalscorer and the youngest player in [[UEFA Champions League]] history to start a knockout phase match, all at the age of 16, before winning his maiden Ligue 1 title. In his second season, he solidified his place as a starter and won a [[Double (association football)#France|domestic double]], before helping PSG win a first-ever [[Treble (association football)#Continental trebles|continental treble]] in his third season.

At the youth international level, Zaïre-Emery has represented France from the [[France national under-16 football team|under-16]] to [[France national under-21 football team|under-21]] levels. In September 2023, he became the youngest [[Captain (association football)|captain]] of the under-21s in thirty years. In November of the same year, Zaïre-Emery scored on his senior debut for France, becoming the team's third-youngest debutant and second-youngest goalscorer.

==Early life==
Warren Marie Jean-Pierre Zaïre-Emery<ref>{{cite web |url=https://fdp.fifa.org/assetspublic/ce233/pdf/SquadLists-English.pdf |title=Squad List: FIFA Club World Cup 2025: Paris Saint-Germain (FRA) |publisher=FIFA |page=26 |date=16 June 2025 |access-date=16 June 2025}}</ref> was born on 8 March 2006 in [[Montreuil, Seine-Saint-Denis|Montreuil]], Seine-Saint-Denis.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/FootballFicheJoueur97236.html |title=Warren Zaïre-Emery |newspaper=L'Équipe |location=Paris |access-date=26 August 2024 |language=fr}}</ref> His father, Franck Emery, was born in [[Aubervilliers]], and also a footballer, having played with [[Red Star FC|Red Star]] in Seine-Saint-Denis.<ref name="BFM">{{Cite web |last=Bouville |first=Hugo |date=14 April 2022 |title=PSG: qui est Warren Zaïre-Emery, le phénomène parisien de 16 ans promis à un brillant avenir |url=https://rmcsport.bfmtv.com/football/ligue-1/psg-qui-est-warren-zaire-emery-le-phenomene-parisien-de-16-ans-promis-a-un-brillant-avenir_AD-202204140693.html |access-date=2022-05-28 |website=[[RMC Sport]] |language=fr}}</ref><ref name="AF">{{Cite web |last1=Delaporte |first1=Augustin |last2=Guégan |first2=Hervé |date=16 Dec 2021 |title=Warren Zaire-Emery, le surdoué du PSG |url=https://www.actufoot.com/warren-zaire-emery-le-surdou%C3%A9-du-psg |access-date=28 May 2022 |website={{ill|actufoot|fr}}}}</ref> His mother is of Martiniquais descent.<ref>{{Cite web |date=28 July 2022 |title=PSG : Warren Zaïre-Emery a des racines à Petit-Bourg en Martinique ! |url=https://globallfoot.com/2022/07/28/psg-warren-zaire-emery-a-des-racines-a-petit-bourg-en-martinique/ |access-date=24 January 2025 |website=globallfoot.com}}</ref>

Zaïre-Emery started playing at [[FCM Aubervilliers|Aubervilliers]] at the age of four, having to wait a year just to be old enough to take his first license there.<ref name="BFM" /><ref name="AF" />

==Club career==
===Paris Saint-Germain===
====Youth career====
Already a standout player for Aubervilliers, Zaïre-Emery was quickly scouted by [[Paris Saint-Germain FC|Paris Saint-Germain]] (PSG), signing with the club from the capital in 2014.<ref name="AF"/> In their [[Paris Saint-Germain Academy|youth system]], Zaïre-Emery always played in categories above his age, impressing his coaches at all levels. During the 2021–22 season, as he had only turned 15, he was the youngest player of the under-19 squad.<ref name="AF" /><ref name="Prsien">{{Cite web |last=Quarez |first=Benjamin |date=2022-03-15 |title=Warren Zaïre-Emery, 16 ans, le nouveau phénomène du PSG : "C'est sûrement ce que j'ai vu de mieux" |url=https://www.leparisien.fr/sports/football/psg/warren-zaire-emery-16-ans-le-nouveau-phenomene-du-psg-cest-surement-ce-que-jai-vu-de-mieux-15-03-2022-QT2AUNDCEVC7DPTUU7I5TBEXTQ.php |access-date=2022-05-28 |website=[[Le Parisien]] |language=fr}}</ref><ref name="LE">{{Cite web |last=Delom |first=Hugo |date=3 Jan 2022 |title=Lavallée, El Hannach, Bodiang, Kari, Zaire-Emery... Qui sont les " titis " de demain du PSG ? |url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Article/Lavallee-el-hannach-bodiang-kari-zaire-emery-les-titis-de-demain-du-psg/1308183 |access-date=2022-05-28 |website=[[L'Équipe]] |language=fr}}</ref><ref name="BFM1">{{Cite web |last1=Jaquin |first1=Alexandre |last2=Tanzi |first2=Loïc |date=1 March 2022 |title=PSG-Séville: qui sont les nouveaux talents du PSG en Youth League? |url=https://rmcsport.bfmtv.com/football/youth-league/psg-seville-qui-sont-les-nouveaux-talents-du-psg-en-youth-league_AV-202203010338.html |access-date=2022-05-28 |website=RMC Ssport |language=fr}}</ref> Despite his young age, Zaïre-Emery  became a key player of the U19s, most notably in December 2021, when he was the standout performer of PSG in the [[2021–22 UEFA Youth League|UEFA Youth League]]: during the last [[2021–22 UEFA Youth League group stage|group stage]] game, helping his team to a 3–2 home win against [[Club Brugge KV|Club Brugge]] with a goal and an assist, narrowly qualifying PSG directly to the [[2021–22 UEFA Youth League knockout phase|round of 16]].<ref name="AF" /><ref name="FM">{{Cite web |last1=Aouna |first1=Santi |last2=Denis |first2=Sebastien |date=6 May 2022 |title=PSG : ça brûle pour Warren Zaïre-Emery |url=https://www.footmercato.net/a1328414553096758864-psg-ca-brule-pour-warren-zaire-emery |access-date=2022-05-28 |website={{ill|Foot Mercato|fr}} |language=fr}}</ref> At the age of 15, Zaïre-Emery was called by [[Mauricio Pochettino]] to the first team that season.<ref name="BFM" /><ref name="AF" /> Attracting the attention of several other big European clubs while still yet to sign his first professional contract,<ref name="FM" /><ref name="11M">{{Cite web |last=Chirat |first=Antoine |date=2022-02-21 |title=PSG : un titi devrait passer pro malgré les convoitises allemandes |url=https://www.onzemondial.com/ligue-1/psg-un-titi-devrait-passer-pro-malgre-les-convoitises-allemandes-761906 |access-date=2022-05-28 |website=[[Onze Mondial]] |language=fr}}</ref> he joined [[Jorge Mendes]]'s agency in March 2022.<ref name="11Mb">{{Cite web |last=Déchelotte |first=Arnaud |date=2022-03-17 |title=PSG : une pépite du club choisit Jorge Mendes comme agent ! |url=https://www.onzemondial.com/transferts/psg-une-pepite-du-club-choisit-jorge-mendes-comme-agent-767024 |access-date=2022-05-28 |website=Onze Mondial |language=fr}}</ref><ref name="Tune">{{Cite web |last=Toison |first=Nicolas |date=2022-03-18 |title=Warren Zaire-Emery rejoint l'agent de Cristiano Ronaldo |url=https://www.sportune.fr/sport-business/football/psg-lagent-de-cristiano-ronaldo-recrute-une-pepite-du-psg-279643 |access-date=2022-05-28 |website=Sportune |language=fr-FR}}</ref>

====2022–23: Debut season and breakthrough====
In July 2022, Zaïre-Emery signed his first professional contract with PSG, a three-year deal until 30 June 2025.<ref>{{Cite web |date=15 July 2022 |title=Warren Zaire-Emery signs his first professional contract |url=https://en.psg.fr/teams/first-team/content/warren-zaire-emery-signs-his-first-professional-contract |access-date=15 July 2022 |publisher=[[Paris Saint-Germain FC]]}}</ref> Under new coach [[Christophe Galtier]], he made his senior debut in a 2–0 [[Friendly (association football)|friendly]] win over [[US Quevilly-Rouen Métropole|Quevilly-Rouen]],<ref>{{Cite web |date=15 July 2022 |title=Paris Saint-Germain V Quevilly Rouen |url=https://en.psg.fr/teams/first-team/fixtures-and-results/202223/paris-saint-germain-v-quevilly-rouen |access-date=25 July 2022 |publisher=[[Paris Saint-Germain FC]] |language=fr}}</ref> and was included in PSG's [[preseason]] tour in Japan, where he was in the starting lineup for a 3–0 win over [[Urawa Red Diamonds]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Urawa Red Diamonds V Paris Saint-Germain |date=23 July 2022 |url=https://en.psg.fr/teams/first-team/fixtures-and-results/202223/urawa-red-diamonds-v-paris-saint-germain |access-date=25 July 2022 |publisher=[[Paris Saint-Germain FC]] |language=fr}}</ref> On 6 August 2022, Zaïre-Emery made his official debut for PSG as a substitute in a 5–0 league win away to [[Clermont Foot|Clermont]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Clermont vs. PSG - 6 August 2022|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2022/08/06/france/ligue-1/clermont-foot-auvergne/paris-saint-germain-fc/3802142/|access-date=6 August 2022}}</ref> His debut at the age of 16 years and 151 days made him the youngest player to appear in an official match for the club, a record which was previously held by [[El Chadaille Bitshiabu]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Zaïre-Emery devient le plus jeune joueur de l'histoire du PSG|url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/Zaire-emery-devient-le-plus-jeune-joueur-de-l-histoire-du-psg/1346993|date=6 August 2022|access-date=6 August 2022|publisher=[[L'Équipe]]|language=fr}}</ref> On 25 October, Zaïre-Emery made his [[UEFA Champions League]] debut as a substitute in a 7–2 home victory over [[Maccabi Haifa F.C.|Maccabi Haifa]]. This made him the youngest player to appear in the Champions League for PSG.<ref>{{Cite web |date=25 October 2022 |title=Zaïre-Emery the club's youngest player in the Champions League! |url=https://en.psg.fr/teams/first-team/content/warren-zaire-emery-the-youngest-paris-saint-germain-player-to-play-in-the-uefa-champions-league-2022-2023-maccabi-haifa-fc |access-date=27 October 2022 |publisher=[[Paris Saint-Germain FC]]}}</ref> On 7 January 2023, he made his first start in a 3–1 [[Coupe de France]] victory away to [[LB Châteauroux|Châteauroux]], becoming the youngest starter in the club's history.<ref>{{Cite web |date=6 January 2023 |title=Warren Zaïre-Emery becomes the youngest starter in the club's history |url=https://en.psg.fr/teams/first-team/content/warren-zaiere-emery-becomes-youngest-starter-in-the-clubs-history-psg-record-coupe-de-france |access-date=9 January 2023 |publisher=[[Paris Saint-Germain FC]]}}</ref> He became the club's youngest starter in Ligue 1 in a 1–0 defeat away to [[Stade Rennais F.C.|Rennes]] eight days later.<ref>{{Cite web |date=15 January 2023 |title=Another record for Warren Zaire-Emery! |url=https://en.psg.fr/teams/first-team/content/another-record-for-warren-zaire-emery-history-paris-saint-germain-ligue-1-2022-2023 |access-date=16 January 2023 |publisher=[[Paris Saint-Germain FC]]}}</ref> On 1 February, Zaïre-Emery scored his first senior goal, coming off the bench to cap off a 3–1 victory against [[Montpellier HSC|Montpellier]]; in doing so he became PSG's youngest ever goalscorer, aged 16 years and 330 days.<ref>{{cite tweet |user=OptaJean |number=1620904280860557312 |title=16&330 - A 16 ans et 330 jours, Warren Zaïre-Emery est devenu le plus jeune buteur de l'histoire de Paris en Ligue 1 |language=fr |date=1 February 2023 }}</ref> On 14 February, he became the youngest player to start a Champions League knockout game at the age of 16 years and 343 days in a 1–0 loss to [[FC Bayern Munich|Bayern Munich]].<ref>{{cite web |last=Hindle |first=Thomas |date=14 February 2023 |title=Who is Warren Zaire-Emery? PSG's 16-year-old wonderkid set to start vs Bayern Munich in Champions League last-16 tie |url=https://www.goal.com/en/news/who-warren-zaire-emery-psg-16-year-old-wonderkid-start-bayern-munich-champions-league-last-16/bltb40858004392256f |access-date=24 January 2025 |publisher=Goal.com}}</ref> At the end of the [[2022–23 Paris Saint-Germain FC season|2022–23 season]], Zaïre-Emery won his first Ligue 1 title.<ref>{{Cite news |date=2023-05-28 |title=PSG wins record 11th French title |language=en |work=Le Monde.fr |url=https://www.lemonde.fr/en/sports/article/2023/05/28/psg-wins-record-11th-french-title_6028225_9.html |access-date=2023-08-27}}</ref>

====2023–24: Establishment as a key player====
[[File:Zaire Emery vs MHSC 18 mars 2024.png|thumb|upright|Zaïre-Emery with [[Paris Saint-Germain FC|Paris Saint-Germain]] in 2024]]

On 26 August 2023, Zaïre-Emery recorded his first assist for PSG, a pass for [[Marco Asensio]] in a 3–1 win over [[RC Lens|Lens]]. It made him the youngest PSG player to record a Ligue 1 assist since [[Opta Sports|Opta]] began analysing this data in 2006.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-08-27 |title=Stats & facts: A look back at the win over Lens |url=https://en.psg.fr/teams/first-team/content/stats-facts-a-look-back-at-the-win-over-lens-paris-saint-germain-ligue-1-2023-2024 |access-date=2023-08-27 |website= |publisher=Paris Saint-Germain |language=en}}</ref> On 4 October, Zaïre-Emery assisted [[Lucas Hernandez]]'s header in a 4–1 Champions League defeat away to [[Newcastle United F.C.|Newcastle United]], making him the youngest French and PSG player to record an assist in the competition.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-10-04 |title=PSG midfielder Warren Zaïre-Emery becomes youngest ever Frenchman to provide an assist in the Champions League - Get French Football News |url=https://www.getfootballnewsfrance.com/2023/psg-midfielder-warren-zaire-emery-becomes-youngest-ever-frenchman-to-provide-an-assist-in-the-champions-league/ |access-date=2023-10-04 |language=en-US}}</ref> Two weeks later, he registered two assists in a 3–0 Champions League victory over [[AC Milan]], becoming the youngest player to reach three assists in the competition. Having won the [[player of the match]] award on the night, he also became the youngest player to make twenty starts for PSG.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-10-25 |title=Warren Zaire-Emery announces arrival in PSG's dominant Champions League win over Milan |url=https://www.cbssports.com/soccer/news/warren-zaire-emery-announces-arrival-in-psgs-dominant-champions-league-win-over-milan/ |access-date=2023-10-26 |website=CBSSports.com |language=en}}</ref> On 29 October, Zaïre-Emery scored his first goal of the season, a "rocket" into the top corner from outside the box, in a 3–2 away victory over [[Stade Brestois 29|Brest]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-10-29 |title=PLAYER RATINGS {{!}} Brest 2 - 3 PSG: Mbappé's brace saves Paris' blushes - Get French Football News |url=https://www.getfootballnewsfrance.com/2023/player-ratings-brest-2-2-psg-mbappes-brace-saves-paris-blushes/ |access-date=2023-10-29 |language=en-US}}</ref> In the following game against Montpellier, he scored his first goal at the [[Parc des Princes]] in a 3–0 Parisian victory.<ref>{{Cite web |date=3 November 2023 |title=Paris reçu 5 sur 5 face à Montpellier ! |url=https://www.psg.fr/equipes/equipe-premiere/content/paris-recu-5-sur-5-face-a-montpellier-compte-rendu-paris-saint-germain-montpellier-herault-sc-ligue-1-2023-2024 |access-date=3 November 2023 |publisher=[[Paris Saint-Germain FC]] |language=Fr}}</ref> On 13 December, he scored his first Champions League goal in a 1–1 away draw against [[Borussia Dortmund]], which qualified his club to the knockout stages.<ref>{{cite web |date=13 December 2023 |title=PSG edge through behind Dortmund as Zaïre-Emery hints at exciting future |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2023/dec/13/borussia-dortmund-psg-champions-league-match-report |access-date=24 January 2025 |work=The Guardian}}</ref> At the age of 17 years and 280 days he became the youngest French goalscorer in Champions League history and PSG's youngest goalscorer in European competitions.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-12-13 |title=Ligue des champions : devant Benzema et Mbappé, Zaïre-Emery plus jeune buteur français de l'histoire de la compétition |url=https://www.lefigaro.fr/sports/football/ligue-des-champions/ligue-des-champions-devant-benzema-et-mbappe-zaire-emery-plus-jeune-buteur-francais-de-l-histoire-de-la-competition-20231213 |access-date=2023-12-13 |website=Le Figaro |language=fr}}</ref>

On 27 April 2024, prior to a home match against [[Le Havre AC|Le Havre]], PSG announced that Zaïre-Emery had extended his contract with the club until 30 June 2029.<ref>{{Cite web |date=27 April 2024 |title=Le Paris Saint-Germain s'inscrit avec Warren Zaïre-Emery jusqu'en 2029 |url=https://www.psg.fr/equipes/equipe-premiere/content/le-paris-saint-germain-sinscrit-avec-warren-zaiere-emery-jusquen-2029-psg-club-new-2023-2024 |access-date=28 April 2024 |publisher=[[Paris Saint-Germain FC]] |language=Fr}}</ref> In the match, he provided an assist for [[Bradley Barcola]]'s goal, PSG's first in a 3–3 draw.<ref>{{Cite web |date=27 April 2024 |title=Paris s'arrache pour refuser la défaite face au Havre ! |url=https://www.psg.fr/equipes/equipe-premiere/content/paris-sarrache-pour-refuser-la-defaite-face-au-havre-compte-rendu-paris-saint-germain-le-havre-ac-ligue-1-2023-2024 |access-date=28 April 2024 |publisher=[[Paris Saint-Germain FC]] |language=Fr}}</ref> The following day, Zaïre-Emery won his second Ligue 1 title with PSG thanks to [[Olympique Lyonnais|Lyon]]'s victory over [[AS Monaco FC|Monaco]].<ref name=":1" /><ref>{{Cite web |title=Ligue 1 : Monaco battu à Lyon, Paris décroche un 12ème titre de Champion de France |url=https://www.lindependant.fr/2024/04/28/ligue-1-monaco-battu-a-lyon-paris-decroche-un-12eme-titre-de-champion-de-france-11919702.php |access-date=2024-04-28 |website=lindependant.fr |language=fr}}</ref> On 13 May, he was awarded the [[Ligue 1 Young Player of the Year]] award at the [[Trophées UNFP du football]] ceremony.<ref name=":L1YP">{{Cite web |title=Warren Zaïre-Emery, élu meilleur espoir de l'année : " Très content de recevoir ce trophée " |url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/Warren-zaire-emery-elu-meilleur-espoir-de-l-annee-tres-content-de-recevoir-ce-trophee/1467407 |access-date=2024-05-13 |website=L'Équipe |language=fr}}</ref> He was also included in the [[Trophées UNFP du football#2023–24|Team of the Year]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Bono |first=Elio |date=2024-05-13 |title=Trophées UNFP : Kylian Mbappé meilleur joueur, le résumé de la soirée |url=https://www.leparisien.fr/sports/football/ligue-1/direct-trophees-unfp-une-5e-recompense-pour-kylian-mbappe-suivez-la-ceremonie-13-05-2024-4GXWIMFU6BHZHIPFQ6RFRSD42I.php |access-date=2024-05-14 |website=leparisien.fr |language=fr-FR}}</ref> On 25 May, Zaïre-Emery started in the [[2024 Coupe de France final]], a 2–1 win for PSG over Lyon.<ref name=":2" />

====2024–25: Continental treble====
On 16 August 2024, Zaïre-Emery started in the first match of the [[2024–25 Ligue 1]] season, a 4–1 victory for PSG over Le Havre.<ref>{{Cite web |date=16 August 2024 |title=Le Havre V Paris Saint-Germain |url=https://www.psg.fr/equipes/equipe-premiere/calendrier-et-resultats/202425/le-havre-v-paris-saint-germain |access-date=17 August 2024 |publisher=[[Paris Saint-Germain FC]] |language=Fr}}</ref> On 23 August, in PSG's first home game, he scored the fifth goal of a 6–0 win over Montpellier, his first of the season. After receiving a pass from [[Ousmane Dembélé]], he [[Nutmeg (association football)|nutmegged]] defender [[Boubakar Kouyaté]] before placing his shot to goalkeeper [[Benjamin Lecomte]]'s left, a goal that was described by ''[[Le Parisien]]'' as "sumptuous".<ref>{{Cite web |last=Rondet |first=Hugo |date=2024-08-23 |title=PSG-Montpellier : le but somptueux inscrit par Warren Zaïre-Emery en vidéo |url=https://www.leparisien.fr/sports/football/ligue-1/psg-montpellier-le-but-somptueux-inscrit-par-warren-zaire-emery-en-video-23-08-2024-2K2REAPZBZFPLELRXDXB2MLAAQ.php |access-date=2024-08-24 |website=leparisien.fr |language=fr-FR}}</ref> On 6 November, he scored in PSG's 2–1 defeat at home to [[Atlético Madrid]] in the Champions League.<ref>{{Cite web |last= |first= |date=2024-11-06 |title=How Zaire-Emery stunned Atletico early on |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/live-blogs/psg-atletico-madrid-live-updates-champions-league-score-result/Wnl6qP4JSYdM/KHWWi0z4makU/ |access-date=2024-12-31 |website=The Athletic |language=en-US}}</ref> On 18 January 2025, Zaïre-Emery started in a 2–1 victory away to [[RC Lens|Lens]] for his 100th match for PSG.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2025-01-18 |title=100th match with Paris Saint-Germain for Warren Zaïre-Emery |url=https://en.psg.fr/teams/first-team/content/100th-match-with-paris-saint-germain-for-warren-zaiere-emery-record-stats-psg-paris-saint-germain-20242025 |access-date=2025-01-21 |website=EN.PSG.FR |language=en}}</ref> He became the youngest player to achieve the feat, at the age of 18 years, 10 months, and 10 days, eclipsing [[Jean-Marc Pilorget]]'s previous record.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2025-01-19 |title=Stats & Facts : Retour sur la victoire à Lens ! |url=https://www.psg.fr/equipes/equipe-premiere/content/stats-facts-retour-sur-la-victoire-a-lens-psg-ligue-1-opta-chiffres-cles-20242025#:~:text=Titulaire%20sur%20la%20pelouse%20du,10%20mois%20et%2010%20jours. |access-date=2025-01-21 |website=PSG.FR |language=fr}}</ref> On 8 March 2025, on his 19th birthday, he wore the captain's armband in a 4–1 win over [[Stade Rennais FC|Rennes]], becoming the second-youngest captain in PSG history after then-17-year-old [[Mamadou Sakho]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Media365 |date=2025-03-08 |title=PSG : Premier brassard de capitaine pour Zaïre-Emery |url=https://sports.orange.fr/football/ligue-1/psg/article/psg-premier-brassard-de-capitaine-pour-zaire-emery-CNT000002hNFIo.html |access-date=2025-03-11 |website=Orange Actualités |language=fr}}</ref> On 5 April 2025, Zaïre-Emery started in the 1–0 win over [[Angers SCO|Angers]] that secured PSG's record-extending thirteenth league title.<ref>{{Cite web |title=PSG 1-0 Angers (Apr 5, 2025) Game Analysis |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/report/_/gameId/706676 |access-date=2025-05-08 |website=ESPN |language=en}}</ref> He came on as a substitute in the [[2025 UEFA Champions League final]], a 5–0 win over [[Inter Milan]] that rounded off PSG's first [[Treble (association football)#Continental trebles|continental treble]].<ref name=":4" />

==== 2025–26 season ====
On 13 August 2025, Zaïre-Emery started in the [[2025 UEFA Super Cup]], participating in PSG's 2–2 draw and 4–3 penalty shoot-out victory over [[Tottenham Hotspur F.C.|Tottenham Hotspur]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=penalties |first=Paris Saint-Germain looked set to miss out on the UEFA Super Cup, but stunned Tottenham with a late comeback before winning on |title='We didn't give up' - Zaire-Emery hails PSG's fight after Super Cup triumph |url=https://www.beinsports.com/en-us/soccer/uefa-super-cup/articles/we-didnt-give-up-zaire-emery-hails-psgs-fight-after-super-cup-triumph-2025-08-13 |access-date=2025-08-14 |website=beIN SPORTS |language=en-us}}</ref> On 9 November, he scored his first goal of the season in a 3–2 win over Lyon, becoming the first player born in 2006 or later to score more than five Ligue 1 goals.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2025-11-11 |title=Stats & facts : Retour sur la victoire à Lyon ! |url=https://www.psg.fr/content/stats-and-facts-olympique-lyonnais-paris-saint-germain-ligue-1-2025-2026 |access-date=2025-12-21 |website=www.psg.fr |language=fr}}</ref> In the [[2025 FIFA Intercontinental Cup final]], playing as a right-back during [[Achraf Hakimi]]'s absence due to injury, Zaïre-Emery was described as one of Paris Saint-Germain's best performers in the match, an eventual victory on penalties over [[CR Flamengo|Flamengo]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Zaïre-Emery : « Ça montre la force qu'on a et l'équipe qu'on est » |url=https://www.culturepsg.com/news/match/zaire-emery-ca-montre-la-force-qu-on-a-et-l-equipe-qu-on-est/58011 |access-date=2025-12-21 |website=CulturePSG |language=fr}}</ref>

==International career==
===Youth===
In April 2022, he was selected with the [[France national under-17 football team|France under-17 national team]] for the [[2022 UEFA European Under-17 Championship|UEFA Under-17 Euro]].<ref name=FM/> With this 2005 generation, he was the only 2006-born player of the squad.<ref name="BFM2">{{Cite web |last=Tanzi |first=Loïc |date=12 May 2022 |title=Euro U17: Tel, Zaire-Emery, Bitshiabu... les talents Scouting RMC à suivre |url=https://rmcsport.bfmtv.com/football/equipe-de-france/euro-u17-tel-zaire-emery-bitshiabu-les-talents-scouting-rmc-a-suivre_AV-202205120560.html |access-date=2022-05-28 |website=RMC Sport |language=fr}}</ref> France went on to win the tournament, with Zaïre-Emery scoring two goals.<ref name=":0"/>

In September 2023, Zaïre-Emery was called up to the [[France national under-21 football team|France under-21s]] by newly appointed coach [[Thierry Henry]]. Henry chose to designate Zaïre-Emery as [[Captain (association football)|team captain]] for the matches against [[Denmark national under-21 football team|Denmark]] and [[Slovenia national under-21 football team|Slovenia]], making him the youngest captain of ''Les Espoirs'' in thirty years.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-09-26 |title=Equipe de France : Zaïre-Emery capitaine des Espoirs, Henry s'explique |url=https://onefootball.com/en/news/equipe-de-france-zaire-emery-capitaine-des-espoirs-henry-sexplique-38180558 |access-date=2023-09-27 |website=OneFootball |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last= |first= |last2= |first2= |date=2023-09-07 |title=" Je voulais voir ce qu'il avait dans le ventre " : Henry adoube Zaïre-Emery comme capitaine des Espoirs |url=https://www.leparisien.fr/sports/football/psg/je-voulais-voir-ce-quil-avait-dans-le-ventre-henry-adoube-zaire-emery-comme-capitaine-des-espoirs-07-09-2023-XXO7K6M6IJC6BKNT4LXSJFAHVI.php |access-date=2023-09-27 |website=leparisien.fr |language=fr-FR}}</ref>

He and his teammate [[Bradley Barcola]] were not included for the [[Football at the 2024 Summer Olympics – Men's tournament|2024 Summer Olympics]] on home soil, as Paris Saint-Germain denied them permission to compete in the tournament.<ref>{{cite web |date=11 June 2024 |title=JO : LA PRÉ-LISTE ACTUALISÉE |trans-title=Olympic Games: The preliminary list updated |url=https://www.fff.fr/article/12680-jo-la-pre-liste-actualisee.html |access-date=24 January 2025 |publisher=[[French Football Federation]] |language=fr}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Salomon |first=Bruno |date=31 May 2024 |title=JO Paris 2024 : Barcola et Zaïre-Emery ne seront pas libérés par le PSG pour rejoindre l'équipe de France olympique |url=https://www.francebleu.fr/sports/football/jo-paris-2024-barcola-et-zaire-emery-ne-seront-pas-liberes-par-le-psg-pour-rejoindre-l-equipe-de-france-olympique-8858769 |access-date=24 January 2025 |website=[[France Bleu]] |language=Fr}}</ref>

===Senior===
On 9 November 2023, Zaïre-Emery received his first call-up to the senior [[France national football team|France national team]], for [[UEFA Euro 2024 qualifying Group B|UEFA Euro 2024 qualifiers]] against [[Gibraltar national football team|Gibraltar]] and [[Greece national football team|Greece]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-11-09 |title=Équipe de France: Deschamps convoque Zaïre-Emery, le nouveau phénomène du foot français |trans-title=French team: Deschamps summons Zaire-Emery, the new phenomenon of French football |url=https://www.lefigaro.fr/sports/football/euro/equipe-de-france-deschamps-convoque-zaire-emery-le-nouveau-phenomene-du-foot-francais-20231109 |access-date=2023-11-09 |website=Le Figaro |language=fr}}</ref> He became the youngest player to be called up for ''Les Bleus'' since [[Maurice Gastiger]] in 1914, and the third-youngest ever.<ref>{{Cite web |title=PSG prodigy Warren Zaïre-Emery gets senior France call! |url=https://www.ligue1.com/Articles/Other-Competitions/2023/11/09/psg-prodigy-warren-zaire-emery-gets-senior-france-call |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231115065004/https://www.ligue1.com/Articles/Other-Competitions/2023/11/09/psg-prodigy-warren-zaire-emery-gets-senior-france-call |archive-date=15 November 2023 |access-date=2023-11-15 |website=Ligue1 COM |language=en}}</ref> He made his debut on 18 November against Gibraltar, scoring a goal in an eventual [[France v Gibraltar (UEFA Euro 2024 qualifying)|14–0]] win for France, the largest victory in the team's history.<ref>{{Cite web |title=France debut goal shows why PSG's young superstar Warren Zaire-Emery is so special |url=https://www.cbssports.com/soccer/news/france-debut-goal-shows-why-psgs-young-superstar-warren-zaire-emery-is-so-special/ |access-date=2023-11-18 |work=CBS Sports |date=18 November 2023 |language=en}}</ref> His goal made him the second-youngest scorer in France's history, only behind Gastiger.<ref>{{Cite web |title=France - Gibraltar : Zaïre-Emery plus jeune buteur de l'histoire des Bleus d'après-guerre... et blessé dans la foulée |date=18 November 2023 |url=https://www.lavoixdunord.fr/1398498/article/2023-11-18/france-gibraltar-zaire-emery-plus-jeune-buteur-de-l-histoire-des-bleus-et-blesse |access-date=2023-11-18 |publisher=La Voix du Nord |language=fr}}</ref> However, in the process of scoring, Zaïre-Emery was on the receiving end of a tackle by Gibraltarian defender [[Ethan Santos]], who was shown a red card after review.<ref>{{Cite web |last= |first= |title=France makes history after putting 14 past hapless Gibraltar |url=https://www.beinsports.com/en-nz/football/uefa-european-championship-qualifiers/articles-video/france-makes-history-after-putting-14-past-hapless-gibraltar-2023-11-18 |access-date=2023-11-19 |website=beIN SPORTS |language=en-nz}}</ref> Zaïre-Emery, who came off injured, was reported to have suffered a "serious ankle sprain" that was projected to keep him out of action until the end of 2023.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-11-19 |title=Warren Zaïre-Emery out for the rest of 2023 following ankle injury on France debut - Get French Football News |url=https://www.getfootballnewsfrance.com/2023/warren-zaire-emery-out-for-the-rest-of-2023-following-ankle-injury-on-france-debut/ |access-date=2023-11-19 |language=en-US}}</ref>

On 16 May 2024, Zaïre-Emery was selected by [[Didier Deschamps]] as one of the twenty-five players to represent France at [[UEFA Euro 2024]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-05-16 |title='Very happy' Warren Zaire Emery asks for exams exception following Euro call-up - Get French Football News |url=https://www.getfootballnewsfrance.com/2024/very-happy-warren-zaire-emery-asks-for-exams-exception-following-euro-call-up/ |access-date=2024-05-31 |website=Get French Football News |language=en-US}}</ref> He went on to make no appearances in the tournament as France reached the semi-finals.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Margueritte |first=Matthieu |date=2 September 2024 |title=EdF : la mise au point de Deschamps sur le cas Zaïre-Emery |url=https://www.footmercato.net/a7806813456328555286-edf-la-mise-au-point-de-deschamps-sur-le-cas-zaire-emery |access-date=24 January 2025 |website=Foot Mercato |language=Fr}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=France-Espagne: les Bleus éliminés de l'Euro 2024 par une Roja supérieure, mais avec quelques regrets |url=https://rmcsport.bfmtv.com/football/euro/france-espagne-les-bleus-elimines-de-l-euro-2024-par-une-roja-superieure-mais-avec-quelques-regrets_AV-202407090858.html |access-date=2025-01-24 |website=RMC Sport |date=9 July 2024 |language=fr}}</ref>

In October 2025, Zaïre-Emery was not called up by Deschamps and instead was demoted to the under-21s.<ref name="lequipe.fr">{{Cite web |title=Warren Zaïre-Emery de retour chez les Bleus : comment son passage par les Espoirs lui a permis de retrouver confiance |url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Article/Warren-zaire-emery-de-retour-chez-les-bleus-comment-son-passage-par-les-espoirs-lui-a-permis-de-retrouver-confiance/1610054 |access-date=2025-12-21 |website=L'Équipe |language=fr}}</ref> After improvements in his performances the following month, he returned to the senior team in November 2025.<ref name="lequipe.fr"/>

==Style of play==
Zaïre-Emery is a midfielder known for his physicality and technical skills. He is effective in both ball recovery and initiating play, contributing to the structure and balance of his team's midfield.<ref name=Prsien/><ref name=AF/><ref name=LE/><ref name="FM" /> Although most commonly used as a [[Box-to-box midfielder|box-to-box]] or [[defensive midfielder]] by PSG, he is able to play in all positions in the midfield.<ref name=":3">{{Cite web |title=Scouting Report: Warren Zaïre-Emery |url=https://www.thescoutingapp.com/blog/scouting-report-warren-za-iuml-re-emery-253 |access-date=2025-01-24 |website=The Scouting App {{!}} Football Player Database |language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-12-26 |title=PROFILE {{!}} Arrested development for PSG's Warren Zaïre-Emery? - Get French Football News |url=https://www.getfootballnewsfrance.com/2024/profile-arrested-development-for-psgs-warren-zaire-emery/ |access-date=2025-01-24 |language=en-US}}</ref> He also has been successfully deployed as a right fullback notably in the absence of Achraf Hakimi during the 2025-26 season.<ref>https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Video/Ligue-1-warren-zaire-emery-l-interview/20225766</ref> Adept at reading the game, he is described as a player with a very mature personality on the pitch while still in his teenage years, able to take on his responsibilities while maintaining a calm and disciplined attitude.<ref name="AF" /><ref name="Prsien" /><ref name="BFM" /><ref name="LE" /> Zaïre-Emery has been praised for his passing, dribbling, and stamina.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-01-06 |title=Impressing the Impressive: Warren Zaïre-Emery |url=https://breakingthelines.com/player-analysis/impressing-the-impressive-warren-zaire-emery/ |access-date=2025-01-24 |website=Breaking the Lines |language=en-GB}}</ref><ref name=":3" />

==Personal life==
At the "Paris for Good" gala event on 16 May 2024, it was revealed that Zaïre-Emery was in a relationship with PSG goalkeeper Océane Toussaint, the women's recipient of the 2022 [[Titi d'Or]] award.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Kulawik |first=François |date=2024-05-20 |title=Warren Zaïre-Emery en couple avec une joueuse du PSG ! |url=https://www.sports.fr/football/psg/warren-zaire-emery-en-couple-avec-une-joueuse-du-psg-833019.html |access-date=2024-05-26 |website=Sports.fr |language=fr-FR}}</ref> They had been previously pictured together at a [[Louis Vuitton]] event in January 2024.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-02-01 |title=PSG : Warren Zaïre-Emery en couple avec une gardienne du club, la rumeur enfle |url=https://fr.blastingnews.com/sport/2024/02/psg-warren-zaire-emery-en-couple-avec-une-gardienne-du-club-la-rumeur-enfle-003796697.html |access-date=2024-05-26 |website=Blasting News |language=fr}}</ref> It was reported that they broke up in October 2025.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Kulawik |first=François |date=2025-10-09 |title=Warren Zaïre-Emery, la rupture amoureuse |url=https://www.sports.fr/people/football-people/warren-zaire-emery-la-rupture-amoureuse-957442.html |access-date=2025-10-29 |website=Sports.fr |language=fr-FR}}</ref>

